  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Medicines - lack of</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) All statutory/mandatory medicines used or expired should be replenished as soon as possible; 
b) All medicine should be locked and their distribution should be controlled; 
c) Consult MSN 1768 for guidance</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Incorrect administration of medicine</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Only a competent person should diagnose and administer medicines; 
b) Check if casualty has any allergies; 
c) Consult &#39;International Medical Guide for Ship&#39;, &#39;The Ship Captain&#39;s Medical Guide&#39; and relevant sections of the IMDG Code; 
d) If necessary contact CIRM (radio medical centre) for advice.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="3">
      <my:Description>Medical Oxygen</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Smoking within the vicinity of medical oxygen is not permitted; 
b) The Manufacturer&#39;s Manual must be consulted for instructions regarding the use and operation of the medical oxygen kit; 
c) Refer to relevant section(s) of IMDG Code regarding oxygen dosage.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="4">
      <my:Description>Use of no-sterile medical equipment</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Only sterile equipment to be used; 
b) All medical equipment must be stored in its designated place;
c)Refer to relevant sections of shipâ€™s medical guide regarding sterilizing procedures.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="5">
      <my:Description>Lack of and/or improper knowledge</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Regular training of crew regarding first aid techniques;
b) First aid kits should be regularly checked and required stock maintained.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="6">
      <my:Description>Biological - infectious disease</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew suspected of suffering from infectious disease should be isolated from the other crew; 
b) Consider a single crewmember be designated as care provider; 
c) Face mask and disposable gloves to be used; 
d) Appropriate professional advice to be sought.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="7">
      <my:Description>Biological - cuts, open wounds, potential for infection</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) First aid provider to use disposable gloves, and face mask as appropriate; 
b) Any clothing impregnated with blood and other bodily fluids to be washed separately or destroyed; 
c) Open wounds to be cleaned, sterilised and dressed; 
d) Treatment area to be thoroughly cleaned and sterilised after treatment; 
e) All sharp tools should be washed and sterilized after use as well, refer to relevant section of medical guide for procedure; 
f) All used needles should be disposed to designated container, should not be mixed with other garbage.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="8">
      <my:Description>Allergic reaction</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>2</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>3</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Medicines to be checked if they have any allergic recommendation</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>1</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>3</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>2</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="9">
      <my:Description>Incorrect storage of medicines</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>1</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>2</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>1</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Medicines to be checked periodically and ensure that are stored in a suitable place.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>1</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="10">
      <my:Description>Controlled Drugs</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>1</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>1</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>1</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>List to be periodically checked/updated according to Medicines Guide.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>1</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
  </my:Hazards>
